investigation.title: Transcriptomic analysis of liver from mice subjected to simulated spaceflight euthanasia, freezing, and tissue preservation protocols
investigation.description: To understand the molecular mechanisms affected by spaceflight, it is essential to achieve high quality sample preservation on-orbit for downstream gene expression analysis. However, sample preservation protocols must also be compatible with available equipment and crew time.

project.funding: NASA Space Biology Program Office, Space Life and Physical Sciences Research and Applications Division

factors: Tissue Homogenate Preservation Time at -80C in RLT Buffer
